items.title: Feid Esenciales
items.description: Producer, singer, and songwriter Feid began his career in the early 2010s as a songwriter for Latin superstars such as J Balvin (“Ginza”) and Reykon (“Secretos”).  In 2016, he released his first hit single “Morena.” In 2019, he released his full-length album 19 with the hit singles “Nuestra Canción” and “Sígueme”.  Listen to an essential of the best from Colombia’s newest hitmaker.  (Photo: ULME/Press)

items.title: Bon Jovi Essentials
items.description: Bon Jovi is one of rock's great success stories. Given their relatively humble beginnings in New Jersey, Jon Bon Jovi & Co. managed to become one of the world's most popular bands - a status they have maintained for over 25 years. Like fellow Jersey-natives Bruce Springsteen & The E-Street Band and Southside Johnny & The Asbury Jukes, the band proved that pairing honest workingman’s rock with guitar-heavy stadium anthems was a winning formula for the mid-‘80s. Although Bon Jovi achieved success with their first two albums, having landed debut single "Runaway" on the Billboard charts in 1984, it was Slippery When Wet (1986) that made the band megastars. Tracks like "You Give Love A Bad Name", "Livin 'On A Prayer" and "Wanted Dead Or Alive" helped lift the album to become the highest selling record of 1987, as well as the band’s best-selling work to date. The sequel, New Jersey (1988) charted five singles on the Billboard Hot 100 - a record for a hard rock band. The endless touring that their popularity demanded eventually took a toll on the band, forcing its members into a brief hiatus, where they focused on other projects. Their 1992 return initiated a second phase of their career, marked by a musical shift reflecting a popular decline in hair metal. Toning down guitar solos and drums, in favor of a more mature sound and expressive lyrics, Bon Jovi managed to both preserve core fans and gain new ones with Keep The Faith (1992) and These Days (1995), which both achieved platinum sales levels. After another break, this time for four years, Bon Jovi returned again in 2000 with megahit "It's My Life," marking a new era for the adaptive rock giants, and proof of their everlasting appeal. (Photo: Rovi)

items.title: Aphex Twin Essentials
items.description: Describing Aphex Twin is tough. He's an inimitable, generational genius — that much is clear. After that, though, it's hard to tell where fact ends and fiction begins. Did he, for instance, spend the '90's living in a converted bank vault in London's Elephant & Castle area? How about the time he (supposedly) turned up to a gig and spun sandpaper instead of records? Or his repeated claim to have purchased a 9,500lb tank to terrorize the neighbors of his remote estate? One thing's for certain — as evinced by numerous classic albums and quality new releases throughout the 2010s and 2020s, Richard D. James remains one of the most pivotal figures in contemporary electronic music. From his early days as an underground provocateur to his formidable cult following today, the legend of AFX/RDJ continues to endure, inspire, & confound. (Photo: Rovi)

items.title: Craig David Essentials
items.description: Craig David broke into the U.K. music scene at 19 years old with the hit single "Fill Me In". Over the last two decades, his music has experimented with pop and dance/club sounds without losing the essence of his vocal range. Listen to the best from Craig David. (Photo: Rovi)

items.title: David Crosby Essentials
items.description: Singer, songwriter and guitarist David Crosby (1941 - 2023) was not only a founding member of folk-rock pioneers the Byrds and Crosby, Stills and Nash, he was also a solo artist whose past couple decades were some of the most prolific years of his career. David Crosby passed away on January 19, 2023, 81 years old. (Photo: Rovi)

items.description: From their first 'Mixtape,' Stray Kids have set out to tell the story of their generation with self-written and self-produced songs. From the banging EDM tracks to the intimate ballads, get lost in the voices of Stray Kids. (Photo: InGrooves)

items.title: Carlos Vives Esenciales
items.description: Colombian telenovela actor-turned-singer/composer Carlos Vives revitalized two of his native land’s traditional musical genres—cumbia and vallenato—for a public yearning to reconnect with its roots. “La Gota Fria,” one of his most popular hits, features traditional vallenato instruments caja, guacharaca and the accordion as well as the rondin, native to the Incas. Vives isn’t only a purveyor of great music but a proponent of culture. (Photo: Sony/Press)

items.title: Pepe Aguilar Esenciales
items.description: Carrying on the great legacy of the Aguilar family in Regional Mexican with pride (and awards), Pepe has created romantic ballads for the ages. (Photo: ONERpm/Press)

items.title: Paul Anka Essentials
items.description:
Legendary singer-songwriter and honorary Rat Pack affiliate Paul Anka has penned and performed hits from "Put Your Head on My Shoulder" to Frank Sinatra's "My Way". Known globally as an original teen heartthrob, these are Paul's Essentials! 

(Photo: Green Hill Productions, press)
